Friday, April 11, 2014

Countdown to NWEA

   Wow! I just realized I have not posted in a looooong time. Sorry! I am
   going to try to do better on posting more frequently. Anyhow, I am
   currently on spring break and enjoy the nice weather Michigan is
   FINALLY having. It is funny how I know I am suppose to be taking a
   break from school, but all I can think about is the looming NWEA MAP
   test we have at the end of the month. I decided to take action and
   create a packet in which my students could have mixed practice of most
   of the concepts on the NWEA. After about three full days of work, I
   came up with the packet below. You can find it in my TpT store. (Just
   click on the picture)
   [Slide01.jpg]
   Here are pictures of a Math page and an ELA page…
   [SAMPLE+Pages+-+NWEA.png]
   For my blog followers. . .Here is a FREEBIE of one math and ELA page
   from the packet. I hope you like it! Click here for your FREEBIE! I
   hope you find it useful.
